FBIS4-52881 "dreas094_c_94019" FBIS-EAS-94-094 Daily Report 14 May 1994 North Korea Cambodian Leader Sends Letter Supporting DPRK Stance Cambodian Leader Sends Letter Supporting DPRK Stance SK1405050194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0414 GMT 14 May 94 SK1405050194 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk sent a letter to the embassy of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea in Phnom Penh on May 7 supporting the statement released by the DPRK Foreign Ministry on April 28 calling for the replacement of the Korean armistice agreement with a peace agreement and for a peace arrangement. The letter declared that the Cambodian people affairm full and eternal support for the independent, peaceful and most patriotic policy advanced by His Excellency Generalissimo Kim Il-song, the respected great leader. It said it is high time that the armistice agreement signed 40 odd years ago was replaced with a genuine, lasting peace one which definitely guarantees a durable peace and security on the Korean peninsula in actuality.
